It's you! You!

244
00:14:20,317 --> 00:14:23,946
Why? We're friends aren't we, Nakanaka?

245
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:27,491
<i>Forgetting me and inviting Komi?</i>
<i>Unacceptable!</i>

246
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:29,952
I don't remember being friends with you.

247
00:14:30,035 --> 00:14:32,413
<i>You're just jealous that Komi came over.</i>

248
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:33,581
<i>You harlot!</i>

249
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:35,666
RUMBLE

250
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:39,628
<i>These two are not very compatible.</i>

251
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:41,547
Thanks for having me!

252
00:14:41,630 --> 00:14:42,923
Good night!

253
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:44,633
Asleep!

254
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:46,802
<i>What was the point of this visit?</i>

255
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:48,554
So, Komi.

256
00:14:49,638 --> 00:14:52,099
Sit next to me.

257
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:54,894
There's a physics formula
I don't understand..

258
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:57,062
N-No! You should sit here.

259
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:58,898
That cushion is of poor quality!

260
00:15:00,441 --> 00:15:03,027
<i>This is how Yamai and Nakanaka</i>

261
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:06,572
<i>sparked off their battle for Komi's heart.</i>

262
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:08,782
WILD GIRLS
BEAST EARS, THE MOVIE

263
00:15:13,787 --> 00:15:16,999
I know, Komi! Want to play a game?

264
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:18,459
Last time was hard, right?

265
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:21,170
I've gathered some games
with easier controls.

266
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:25,174
<i>Nakanaka's attack:</i>
<i>"For Komi's Benefit."</i>

267
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:27,801
<i>I thought we came to study…</i>

268
00:15:27,885 --> 00:15:29,929
Of course she doesn't want to play.

269
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:31,680
-That's such a boyish activity.
-HEH

270
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:34,391
-What?
-<i>But it was blocked!</i>

271
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:36,226
Girls like romance!

272
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:38,145
Komi, who's your crush?

273
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:39,521
Mine is you.

274
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,231
<i>"Practically a Confession!"</i>

275
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:44,485
YAMAI'S ATTACK: PRACTICALLY A CONFESSION!

276
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:46,487
<i>It's not very effective…</i>

277
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:48,197
Um, what about studying?

278
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:53,661
That reminds me…

279
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,956
I noticed when I entered this room.

280
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:01,543
The whole interior is black and you have
so many anime and movie posters.

281
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:04,505
It's like an otaku boy's room.

282
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:05,589
Urgh!

283
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:07,007
<i>It's super effective!</i>

284
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:08,884
Alright then.

285
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:12,054
What do you consider a girly room?

286
00:16:12,137 --> 00:16:13,722
That's easy.

287
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,224
You need a big mirror.

288
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:18,644
Make-up, perfume, pink items,
antique-style furniture.

289
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:20,854
And serve jasmine tea, not barley…

290
00:16:22,731 --> 00:16:23,816
How basic.

291
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:26,151
<i>It's super effective!</i>

292
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:29,822
Your nails are filthy!
I'm not interested in your opinion.

293
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:32,449
You're the one with damaged hair!

294
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,535
Since you change the color often.

295
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:37,454
You live at home,
so I bet you can't even cook!

296
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:38,914
So unfeminine.

297
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:40,165
-Femininity!
-GIRLS ARE SCARY.

298
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:43,210
Don't judge me on something
you can't even quantify!

299
00:16:43,293 --> 00:16:46,547
According to our star charts,
I'm a better match for Komi!

300
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:48,424
There you go being basic again!

301
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:50,092
There's no evidence!

302
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:52,428
Why do you talk like that?

303
00:16:52,511 --> 00:16:55,514
You do it because
you're an internet addict, right?

304
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:58,517
You're as good at
finding information as my mom!

305
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:01,228
-How old did you say you were?
-<i>Komi is…</i>

306
00:17:01,311 --> 00:17:02,479
-Let's calm down…
-Huh?!

307
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:03,856
Oh, nothing.

308
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:07,067
Komi, which of us is a better friend?

309
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:10,320
<i>And now the spears point at Komi.</i>

310
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,958
YOU'RE BOTH IMPORTANT TO ME.

311
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:34,178
-SECRETLY HAPPY
-FIDGETY

312
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,597
Y-Yeah, but!

313
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:39,433
If you had to choose, who would it be?

314
00:17:40,642 --> 00:17:43,145
Why not see who gets a higher test score?

315
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:44,480
Shut up.

316
00:17:44,563 --> 00:17:46,648
<i>They're in perfect sync.</i>

317
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:51,361
<i>We can't keep asking Komi.</i>

318
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:53,280
<i>She'll hate me if I'm aggressive.</i>

319
00:17:53,363 --> 00:17:55,824
<i>Have you ever not been aggressive?</i>

320
00:17:55,908 --> 00:18:00,788
Isn't there something?
Some way to settle this?

321
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:02,331
Games.

322
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:06,085
We have video games!

323
00:18:09,838 --> 00:18:10,881
Yeah.

324
00:18:10,964 --> 00:18:13,300
Let's do it!

325
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:15,761
-Games!
-Me too!

326
00:18:17,012 --> 00:18:19,890
Hang on! Don't put a banana there!

327
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:23,894
-I'll let my strategy speak for itself!
-Yes, that's it!

328
00:18:23,977 --> 00:18:26,396
Scoundrel! You're aiming
that red carapace at me!

329
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:28,857
Must be your imagination!

330
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:30,567
Take that!

331
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:33,028
The R button on the right…

332
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:36,281
Take that! And that!

333
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:38,242
Boom!

334
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:40,702
Finish!

335
00:18:41,411 --> 00:18:44,164
Yay! I win!

336
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:47,668
That means Komi's best friend is me!

337
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:49,419
BANG

338
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:53,173
<i>Najimi, why do you have to be like that?</i>

339
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:55,801
<i>They competed on their tests too.</i>

340
00:18:56,343 --> 00:18:57,886
A draw?!

341
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,848
You've all cleared your desks, right?

342
00:19:00,931 --> 00:19:02,891
You've got your writing tools?

343
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,811
If you drop anything
I'll get it, so let me know.

344
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:07,855
Now, start!

345
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:30,544
WOBBLE

346
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:36,216
POP

347
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:41,430
<i>Komi only prepared two pencils.</i>

348
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:50,522
HAS TO SAY SHE DROPPED HER PENCIL…

349
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:54,401
<i>Komi is too shy about standing out</i>
<i>so she can't say it.</i>

350
00:19:58,155 --> 00:20:01,366
<i>Huh? Komi's…</i>

351
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,243
<i>not writing…?</i>

352
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:04,828
PLOP

353
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:08,040
<i>Oh, I get it.</i>

354
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:12,920
<i>Around there.</i>

355
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:19,259
Teacher? I dropped my mechanical pencil.

356
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:22,137
-Huh?
-Uh, sorry.

357
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:24,014
Could you get it for me?

358
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:25,432
Sure.

359
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,772
Hm? Is this yours, Komi?

360
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:37,069
You're the only one in this class
who uses a pencil, after all. Here.

361
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:40,864
<i>All set.</i>

362
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:44,159
-Here.
-Oh, thank you.

363
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:47,496
JAPANESE HISTORY TERM FINAL
CLASS 1-1, HITOHITO TADANO

364
00:20:47,579 --> 00:20:49,748
<i>Komi's so clumsy.</i>

365
00:20:50,332 --> 00:20:51,375
<i>Huh?</i>

366
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:54,169
<i>Wait, what?</i>

367
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:55,087
CLUMSY

368
00:20:55,170 --> 00:20:57,631
<i>I forgot to get my eraser out!</i>

369
00:20:57,714 --> 00:21:01,593
I CAN'T MAKE ANY MISTAKES!

370
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:20,904
Excuse me!

371
00:21:20,988 --> 00:21:23,323
I dropped my eraser.

372
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:24,866
Again?

373
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:26,660
I'm sorry.

374
00:21:26,743 --> 00:21:27,786
Here.

375
00:21:27,869 --> 00:21:30,247
Thank you very much.

376
00:21:31,248 --> 00:21:33,875
<i>Is this alright?</i>

377
00:21:43,468 --> 00:21:47,264
<i>Neither of them could focus on the test.</i>

378
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:20,357
BONUS SCENE

379
00:23:29,616 --> 00:23:30,617
Huh?

380
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:37,833
Hey, lend me your eraser.

381
00:23:37,916 --> 00:23:39,042
Huh?

382
00:23:45,048 --> 00:23:46,008
No.

383
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:47,467
Huh? Why?

384
00:23:48,302 --> 00:23:50,429
<i>The eraser became a family heirloom.</i>

385
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:51,922
Subtitle translation by: Claire Tanaka

